{"id": 4608, "title": "Ticket #4608: VirtualMemory attribute not set correction in dynamic slots", "description": "<blockquote>\nWe can now have cgroups enforce a limit on the amount of swap space used per job.  However, dynamics slots advertise the total amount of swap space on the system, not a per-slot value.\n\n<p>Having the job specify a request_swap seems user-hostile -- it is unlikely that a user will know how much swap their job needs.  Instead, the start should have a simple heuristic for swap used base on the Memory attribute of the partition.</p></blockquote>", "remarks": "<blockquote>\n</blockquote>", "derived_tickets": "", "attachments": "", "check_ins": "<table border=\"0\" cellpadding=\"0\" cellspacing=\"0\">\n<tbody><tr><td align=\"right\" valign=\"top\" width=\"160\">2015-Sep-14 16:28</td>\n<td align=\"center\" valign=\"top\" width=\"30\">\n<span class=\"icon dot\">\u00a0</span></td>\n<td align=\"left\" valign=\"top\"> \nCheck-in <span class=\"chng\"><a href=\"chngview?cn=45842\">[45842]</a></span>: Document <span class=\"ticket\"><a class=\"resolved\" href=\"/tickets?ticket=4608\" onclick=\"get_ticket_and_populate_wrapper('4608'); return false;\" title=\"VirtualMemory attribute not set correction in dynamic slots\">#4608</a></span>  (By Greg Thain )</td></tr>\n<tr><td align=\"right\" valign=\"top\" width=\"160\">2015-Apr-15 11:30</td>\n<td align=\"center\" valign=\"top\" width=\"30\">\n<span class=\"icon dot\">\u00a0</span></td>\n<td align=\"left\" valign=\"top\"> \nCheck-in <span class=\"chng\"><a href=\"chngview?cn=44617\">[44617]</a></span>: correct ticket number and LaTeX formatting <span class=\"ticket\"><a class=\"resolved\" href=\"/tickets?ticket=4608\" onclick=\"get_ticket_and_populate_wrapper('4608'); return false;\" title=\"VirtualMemory attribute not set correction in dynamic slots\">#4608</a></span>  (By Karen Miller )</td></tr>\n<tr><td align=\"right\" valign=\"top\" width=\"160\">2015-Apr-15 10:50</td>\n<td align=\"center\" valign=\"t